      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a huge improvement, the language is much more appropriate for the venue. \n\nI just ran a quick check on the density using the formula, and the score for this version is around 0.18. It's okay, but honestly, if we can get that score up to at least 0.25 or 0.30, the algorithm should push us much higher in the search results for the reviewers.\n\nCan you try to expand it further? Try to integrate more specific terminology related to the cellular mechanisms or the spectral composition involved. Just please keep it coherent—don't let the technicality make it unreadable, I really don't want it to look like a bunch of buzzwords just thrown together.",
      "source": "evaluator",
